## Final acceptance

☐ Multiple projects can concurrently submit, observe, cancel, and recover runs
  against one DFHack instance.
☐ Live Busted execution remains strictly serialized and cleanup-gated.
☐ Structured version 2 events and snapshots are the authoritative feedback
  contract.
☐ Each project defaults to one replaceable result file beneath
  `tests/.test-results/dwarfspec/`.
☐ Persistence failure is project-local and cleanup failure is executor-global.
☐ Source and packaged behavior match.
☐ Remote execution and runner UI work remain explicitly outside this completed
  implementation scope.
